a player makes a roll of two six-sided die
  if the total of the faces is 7 or 11 the player wins
  if the sum is 2, 3, or 12, the player loses. 
  if the sum is 4,5,6,8,9, or 10, that sum becomes the players "point"
    the player rolls again until the roll their point. if they roll a 7 before making their point, they lose.